<body><div class=WordSection1>
<div class="brand">📚 ENGLISH CODING · 영어코딩</div>
<h1>🗿 M003 Week 5 — English Worksheet (Beginner)</h1>
<p><strong>Topic:</strong> Recreate the Statues (x, y, z) · <strong>Course:</strong> 3D Coordinates · <strong>Level:</strong> Beginner · <strong>Time:</strong> about 30 minutes</p>
<p>A statue is just blocks <strong>stacked up</strong>. A little body, then a head on top. Every block needs <strong>three</strong> numbers: <strong>(x, y, z)</strong>. x is <strong>across</strong>, y is <strong>up</strong>, z is <strong>forward</strong>. To go higher, change the <strong>2nd number (y)</strong>.</p>
<h3>🧭 Every coordinate is <strong>(x, y, z)</strong></h3>
<div style="display:flex; gap:8px; flex-wrap:wrap; margin:6px 0 2px"><div style="flex:1; min-width:120px; background:#fff3ea; border:1px solid #ffd9c2; border-radius:8px; padding:8px 12px"><b style="color:#e0681c">1st = X</b><br>across →</div><div style="flex:1; min-width:120px; background:#f0ecff; border:1px solid #d9cdff; border-radius:8px; padding:8px 12px"><b style="color:#6b4ee6">2nd = Y</b><br>up ↑ (height)</div><div style="flex:1; min-width:120px; background:#e8f7ef; border:1px solid #c4ead6; border-radius:8px; padding:8px 12px"><b style="color:#1a8f5a">3rd = Z</b><br>forward ⤴</div></div>

<blockquote>
<p>🔴 Stand on your <strong>home spot</strong> (red block) every run. Move your feet, move your head.</p>
</blockquote>
<hr />
<h2>1 · Predict 🔮</h2>
<p>Read the blocks. Look at the numbers. Do <strong>not</strong> run it.</p>
<pre><code>place gray block at (3, 0, 3)
place gray block at (3, 1, 3)
place gray block at (3, 2, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Across, up, or deeper? Circle one. Which number changes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<pre><code>place gray block at (3, 0, 3)
place gray block at (4, 0, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Across, up, or deeper? Circle one. Which number changes?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>2 · Spot the Bug 🐛</h2>
<p>The head should sit <strong>on top</strong> of the body. To go up, the <strong>2nd number (y)</strong> must be <strong>bigger</strong>. Here the head uses the <strong>same y</strong> as the body, so it hides inside.</p>
<pre><code># buggy — head inside the body
place gray block at (3, 1, 3)
place white block at (3, 1, 3)
</code></pre>
<p>Fix it. The body is at y = 1, so the head must go one higher.</p>
<pre><code># fixed
place gray block at (3, 1, 3)
place white block at (3, ____, 3)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Word bank:</strong> <code>0</code> · <code>1</code> · <code>2</code></p>
<p><strong>Write the missing number:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was the buggy one wrong? One short sentence.</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>3 · Build It 📸</h2>
<p><strong>Warm-up:</strong> in your world, place 2 gray blocks on top of each other — a little body.</p>
<p><strong>Now build a small statue.</strong> Stack 3 gray blocks for the body, then 1 white block on top for the head.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>🧱 Recipe (stand on your home spot first, feet on the ground y = 0):
- body: gray at (3, 0, 3), then (3, 1, 3), then (3, 2, 3)
- head: white at (3, 3, 3)</p>
</blockquote>
<p>If you finish early, try the big one: make the body taller.</p>
<p>Send a <strong>photo or video</strong>, then write 2 sentences.</p>
<blockquote>
<p>I built a statue with a body and a …</p>
<p>To go up I changed the … number.</p>
</blockquote>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h2>4 · Explain It 🎥</h2>
<p>Take a short video of your statue. Try to use these words: <strong>x</strong>, <strong>y</strong>, <strong>z</strong>, <strong>up</strong>.</p>
<blockquote>
<ol>
<li>Stand on your home spot.</li>
<li>Point at the body and read one block: "x …, y …, z …".</li>
<li>Point at the head and say which number made it go up.</li>
</ol>
</blockquote>
<p><strong>Write the 2 sentences you will say.</strong> You can read them while filming.</p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<hr />
<h3>Submit ✅</h3>
<p>Send this worksheet + your walkthrough video to teacher on KakaoTalk.</p>
<div class="footer">영어코딩 · <b>english-coding.co.uk</b></div>
</div></body></html>
